						               													<description>Cim is an abstract game for two to four players, played on a fifteen by fifteen rectangular grid. Each player attempts to arrange a set of Miwin's Dice (numbers III, IV, and V in the family) into the shape of an isosceles right triangle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Placement of dice is constrained by their distance on the grid from other dice. During initial placement, dice are placed exactly n units away from the last die placed (which has n pips showing). Once all dice are on the board, a player may re-position one of her own dice with respect to the pips showing on any other die on the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
